en_123237_0	A special grand felicitation ceremony to praise and appreciate the wheelchair expedition, ‘Perseverance’ of Corporal Gemunu Karunarathna of 6 Gajaba Regiment got underway at Saliyapura Gajaba Regiment (GR) Headquarters on Wednesday (12) with the participation of more than 100 wheelchair-ridden War Heroes and Major General Shavendra Silva, Colonel of the Regiment, GR.
en_123237_1	Kapruka (Pvt) Ltd, appreciative of the arrangement awarded a special gift to the adventurer who within a matter of 8 days covered a distance of 580 km from Point Dondra and reached Point Pedro on Tuesday (11) ending his wheelchair expedition, one of the firsts in the Army, perhaps in the entire island.
en_123237_2	The felicitation ceremony attended by the Colonel of the Regiment, GR, Centre Commandant and Kapruka (Pvt) Ltd representatives also saw Corporal Gemunu Karunarathna gifted with a cheque of Rs 1 lakh by Major General Shavendra Silva on behalf of All Ranks in the GR.
en_123237_3	In addition, the sponsors gave away special gift parcels to all 100 differently able War Heroes who graced the event.
en_123237_4	Their family members are also to be provided with gift hampers during the festive season as a special regard to the War Heroes.
en_123237_5	Brigadier Harendra Peiris, GR Center Commandant welcomed the day’s protagonist on arrival at the GR Headquarters and conducted him to the auditorium in a procession before the ceremony commenced.
en_123237_6	The ceremony appreciated the determination and courage of the amputated War Hero who brought pride and admiration to the Gajaba Regiment in particular and the Army in general.
en_123237_7	During his upward journey, GR Headquarters at Saliyapura conducted a separate reception in front of the Headquarters entrance with a view to boosting the morale of all military personnel and sportsmen alike.
en_123237_8	Major General Shavendra Silva shared a few words with him and assured him of all possible support in future too as he has now made the Gajaba family proud.
en_123237_9	Senior Officers and a large gathering of GR War Heroes, other rankers and family members of the adventurer participated in the felicitation ceremony.
